  "body": "\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: \r\nButton `Chat` is moved outside of the card if username is too long in Discover, Discover -> Popular hashtags -> All and in Discover -> Recent Statuses -> All \r\n![img_2543](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/33633133-0d819ab2-da10-11e7-8214-410a7224f35a.jpg)\r\n\r\n![img_2544](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/33633127-09439db0-da10-11e7-8617-d8661202f2e0.jpg)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nIf user name is too long to fit on the card with button Chat then end of the username is removed and \"...\" is shown, like here (from the release 0.9.12):\r\n\r\n![screenshot_20171205-225650](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/33633281-95561742-da10-11e7-9dd9-2b095d5d56dd.png)\r\n![screenshot_20171205-225654](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/33633289-99e7447a-da10-11e7-8b06-344e3ccd2930.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nIf name is too long then it's not cut but button `Chat` is moved outside of the card or outside of the edges\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status \r\n- Add some contact with a long username e.g. \"Username is long enough to check how it's shown on Discover\" and some hashtag in status (below username) \r\n- That contact should add you as a contact too\r\n- Add some hashtag in status (below username) e.g. #test\r\n- As another contact: add some hashtag to the status, e.g. #test\r\n- open Discover\r\n- Check how button Chat is shown next to the long username\r\n- open All for 2 sections: Popular hashtags and Recent Statuses to check how button Chat is shown there\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly build 96. Status version 0.9.10-422-g6d5251ad\r\n* Operating System: \r\nreal device Pixel XL, Android 8.0\r\nreal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.3.1\r\n\r\n",
