    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The same behaviour as above on Android on Popular #hashtags, Recent statuses: \r\n![screenshot_2017-12-19-16-03-25](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/34161649-fa3e81d4-e4d9-11e7-9fc0-0a608e35425e.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nSimilar on 'Popular #hashtags' -> 'All', 'Recent statuses' -> 'All' screen view:\r\n![pop_hashtg_all_4_5_inch](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/34161470-7024758a-e4d9-11e7-8b15-05e4f47ebb1a.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nOn a wider screen (5.5”) on Android devices there is the same gap as described above for iPhone7\r\n\r\nWhat happens at the moment on ‘Popular #hashtags’, ‘Recent statuses’ cards on Discover tab is that we have a limit of 20 chars (so 17 chars + three dots). On ‘Popular #hashtags’ -> ‘ALL’, ‘Recent statuses’ -> ‘ALL’ list of cards limit is 30 chars (27 chars + 3 dots) \r\nSo it keeps the issue on small width of screen and introduces the gap on wide screen (like 5.5” devices)\r\nIt would be great dynamically fit the ‘Chat’ button next to username length, depending of the screen width.",
